<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="title">About Rooted in Winnipeg</h1>

    <div class="content">
      <p>
        <strong>Rooted in Winnipeg</strong> is a WEBD-3011 e-commerce project that models a real
        local plant shop expanding from in-store sales into a full online storefront.
      </p>
      <p>
        The project focuses on building a practical Rails commerce experience end-to-end:
        product browsing, category navigation, search/filtering, customer accounts, cart + checkout,
        tax calculation by province, and order history.
      </p>
    </div>

    <article class="message is-primary">
      <div class="message-header">
        <p>Project Scope</p>
      </div>
      <div class="message-body">
        <ul>
          <li>Rails 8 + PostgreSQL architecture using standard MVC conventions</li>
          <li>Category-based plant catalog with pagination and keyword search</li>
          <li>Session cart and checkout flow with snapshot-based order totals</li>
          <li>Customer authentication and account-linked order tracking</li>
          <li>Stripe-ready payment integration path for capstone milestones</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="message is-info">
      <div class="message-header">
        <p>Data Model & Integrity</p>
      </div>
      <div class="message-body">
        <ul>
          <li>Products belong to categories and include real botanical attributes</li>
          <li>Users are linked to provinces to support GST/PST/HST tax logic</li>
          <li>Orders store immutable financial snapshots for historical accuracy</li>
          <li>Order items preserve unit price at purchase time for audit-safe totals</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="message is-link">
      <div class="message-header">
        <p>Seed Data Source</p>
      </div>
      <div class="message-body">
        <ul>
          <li>Plant records are sourced from the Perenual API</li>
          <li>Categories and regional tax data are seeded locally in-app</li>
          <li>A <code>PERENUAL_API_KEY</code> is required for full product seeding</li>
          <li>Fallback values/images keep seed runs resilient when API fields are missing</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </article>

    <div class="content">
      <p>
        This project (tries) to follow an incremental build style: complete one working feature at a time, then move to the next.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>